parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ball joints can cause the vehicle to vibrate, pull to one side, and lose control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates while driving
the vehicle pulls to one side
the vehicle is hard to control
the vehicle veers into other lanes
the tire pops off
the vehicle wanders or drifts while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of tire tread can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. Tire cracking can also lead to blowouts, further increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Tires lose tread without losing air pressure
tires blow out
cracking appears on the tire surface.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A tire blowout can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Tires blow out
loss of air pressure
sudden loss of vehicle control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unexpected Engine Shutdown and Limp Mode
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shutdown of the engine while driving can cause a loss of power, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when towing a vehicle on a high-speed highway. This issue can also lead to a loss of control, potentially resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine shuts down without warning
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the wrench symbol appears on the dashboard screen
the vehicle loses power
and the engine stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel pressure sensor can cause the engine to shut down, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine shuts down without warning
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the wrench symbol appears on the dashboard screen
the vehicle loses power
and the engine stalls while driving.
